---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'healthcare-system', text: 'Healthcare System', level: 2 },
  { id: 'visa-requirements', text: 'Visa Options', level: 2 },
  { id: 'insurance-requirements', text: 'Insurance Requirements', level: 2 },
  { id: 'recommended-providers', text: 'Recommended Providers', level: 2 },
  { id: 'costs', text: 'Expected Costs', level: 2 },
  { id: 'scenarios', text: 'Real-World Scenarios', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Iceland Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/iceland/insurance' },
  { title: 'Insurance for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors' },
  { title: 'Norway for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/norway' },
  { title: 'Denmark for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/denmark' },
  { title: 'UK for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/uk' },
];

const providerColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'entryAge', header: 'Max Entry Age' },
  { key: 'renewal', header: 'Renewal' },
  { key: 'monthlyFrom', header: 'From (65-69)' },
  { key: 'icelandFit', header: 'Iceland Fit' },
];

const providerRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'ISK 55,000-78,000/mo', icelandFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'BUPA Global', entryAge: '79', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'ISK 65,000-92,000/mo', icelandFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'ISK 50,000-72,000/mo', icelandFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'AXA Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'ISK 47,000-68,000/mo', icelandFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Icelandic Health Insurance', entryAge: 'No limit', renewal: 'N/A', monthlyFrom: 'Tax-funded', icelandFit: 'For Residents' },
];

const costColumns = [
  { key: 'category', header: 'Expense' },
  { key: 'monthly', header: 'Monthly' },
  { key: 'annual', header: 'Annual' },
];

const costRows = [
  { category: 'International Insurance (65-69)', monthly: 'ISK 50,000-78,000', annual: 'ISK 600,000-936,000' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (70-74)', monthly: 'ISK 70,000-105,000', annual: 'ISK 840,000-1,260,000' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (75-79)', monthly: 'ISK 95,000-142,000', annual: 'ISK 1,140,000-1,704,000' },
  { category: 'Icelandic Public Healthcare', monthly: 'Tax-funded', annual: 'Small co-pays' },
  { category: 'Private Supplement', monthly: 'ISK 8,000-20,000', annual: 'ISK 96,000-240,000' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Health Insurance for Seniors in Iceland 2026 | Retirement Guide"
  description="Guide to health insurance for seniors retiring in Iceland. Northern Lights, geothermal wonders, excellent healthcare, and coverage for expats 65+."
  headline="Health Insurance for Seniors in Iceland"
  subheadline="Iceland offers otherworldly landscapes, excellent healthcare, and Nordic quality of life—though high costs and limited immigration pathways apply."
  heroImage="/images/countries/iceland-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Senior Plans →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Why Seniors Choose Iceland</h2>
  <p>
    Iceland offers unmatched natural wonders—Northern Lights, geysers, glaciers, hot springs—combined with Nordic efficiency and excellent healthcare. The country is remarkably safe, English is widely spoken, and the geothermal heating makes winters surprisingly comfortable indoors.
  </p>

  <p>
    Reykjavík provides capital living with cultural offerings and best healthcare access. The Golden Circle area offers dramatic landscapes with reasonable distance to the capital. Akureyri in the north provides smaller-town living with good hospital. The entire country is within reach.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Key Facts for Seniors</h3>
    <ul class="text-primary-800 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Healthcare:</strong> Excellent; comprehensive public system</li>
      <li><strong>Language:</strong> Icelandic; English widely spoken</li>
      <li><strong>Cost of Living:</strong> ISK 500,000-900,000/month (~$3,500-6,300); very high</li>
      <li><strong>Climate:</strong> Subarctic maritime; milder than expected</li>
      <li><strong>EU Status:</strong> Not EU but EEA member; Schengen zone</li>
      <li><strong>Nature:</strong> Geysers, Northern Lights, glaciers, hot springs</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2 id="healthcare-system">Iceland's Healthcare System</h2>
  <p>
    Iceland has universal healthcare funded through taxes and managed by Icelandic Health Insurance (Sjúkratryggingar Íslands). Quality is excellent—modern facilities, well-trained staff. Landspítali University Hospital in Reykjavík handles complex cases. For very specialized care, some travel to Denmark.
  </p>

  <p>
    Co-payments are minimal. Dental and physiotherapy have separate costs. Wait times vary—urgent care is immediate; elective procedures may wait. Geothermal hot springs and pools are part of Icelandic wellness culture and often recommended for joint health.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">Small Population Reality</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800 mb-0">
      Iceland has only 380,000 people—some highly specialized services aren't available locally. For complex surgeries or rare conditions, Icelanders travel to Denmark or other Scandinavian countries (often covered). Consider this if you have specific medical needs requiring specialized care.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="visa-requirements">Visa Options for Seniors</h2>
  <p>
    Iceland's immigration for non-EEA retirees is restrictive:
  </p>

  <h3>Family Reunification</h3>
  <p>
    If you have an Icelandic citizen spouse or close family, family reunification is possible. Your Icelandic sponsor must meet income requirements.
  </p>

  <h3>Self-Employment</h3>
  <p>
    Starting a business in Iceland can provide residence if beneficial to Iceland's economy. High bar for most retirees but possible for those with business interests.
  </p>

  <h3>EEA/EFTA Citizens</h3>
  <p>
    Free movement applies for EU, Norway, Liechtenstein, and Switzerland citizens. Register after 3 months. Demonstrate sufficient resources and health coverage.
  </p>

  <h3>No Retirement Visa</h3>
  <p>
    Iceland doesn't have a retirement visa for non-EEA nationals. You need qualifying circumstances like family, work, or business.
  </p>

  <h2 id="insurance-requirements">Insurance Requirements</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance requirements for Iceland:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Residence application:</strong> Comprehensive health insurance required</li>
    <li><strong>EEA citizens:</strong> EHIC initially; register for Icelandic coverage</li>
    <li><strong>After registration:</strong> Full access to Icelandic healthcare</li>
    <li><strong>Travel coverage:</strong> Consider coverage for Denmark (specialized care)</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Insurance Strategy for Iceland</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800 mb-0">
      International insurance is essential for residence applications. Once registered, Icelandic healthcare is excellent. Some maintain international coverage for travel and as backup for specialized care in Denmark or elsewhere. Iceland's small population means some specialties require travel.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="recommended-providers">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>
  <p>
    For seniors in Iceland, these providers offer appropriate coverage:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />

  <h3>Why These Providers Work for Iceland</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Good Nordic network, covers Denmark</li>
    <li><strong>BUPA Global:</strong> Highest entry age (79), comprehensive coverage</li>
    <li><strong>Allianz Care:</strong> Competitive European pricing</li>
    <li><strong>Danish access:</strong> Ensure coverage for specialized care travel</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Get Personalized Senior Quotes</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Compare coverage from providers that work well for Iceland.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get BUPA Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="costs">Expected Insurance Costs</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance costs for Iceland are high, reflecting expensive local healthcare:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={costColumns} rows={costRows} />

  <h3>Cost-Saving Strategies</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Get registered:</strong> Icelandic healthcare is excellent once in system</li>
    <li><strong>Iceland exclusion:</strong> Once registered, exclude from international</li>
    <li><strong>Scandinavia coverage:</strong> Include Denmark for specialized care travel</li>
    <li><strong>Geothermal wellness:</strong> Hot springs are free/cheap and therapeutic</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="scenarios">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 1: American with Icelandic Spouse, 67</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> Married to Icelandic citizen. Moving to Reykjavík via family reunification.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Cigna Global for application. After registration, Icelandic system. Keep Cigna for US visits.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> Initially ~ISK 65,000/month. After: public (minimal co-pays) + Cigna (Iceland excluded) ~ISK 45,000/month.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 2: Danish EEA Citizen, 72</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> EEA rights. Moving from Copenhagen for adventure. Danish pension €2,200/month.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> EEA freedom of movement. Register for Icelandic healthcare. BUPA for Denmark visits.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> Icelandic public + BUPA (Iceland excluded) ~ISK 50,000/month (~€350).</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 3: British Nature Photographer, 68</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> Post-Brexit, needs visa pathway. Has Icelandic business partner.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Self-employment visa through photography business. BUPA Global comprehensive.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> BUPA ~ISK 75,000/month (~£500). Northern Lights at doorstep.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Can non-EEA retirees move to Iceland?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Very difficult. Iceland doesn't have a retirement visa. You need: Icelandic spouse/family (reunification), work permit, or viable business. Pure financial independence isn't a pathway. EEA citizens (EU plus Norway, Liechtenstein, Switzerland) have freedom of movement.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">How expensive is Iceland really?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Very expensive—among the world's highest costs. Restaurant meals ISK 3,000-6,000 (~$22-44). Groceries are expensive. However, geothermal heating is cheap, healthcare is covered, and basic costs like swimming pools are subsidized. Budget carefully.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is winter in Iceland bearable?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Surprisingly yes. Geothermal heating means homes are very warm. Temperatures rarely drop below -10°C in Reykjavík (Gulf Stream effect). Main challenge is darkness—only 4-5 hours of daylight in December. Hot springs, pools, and Northern Lights help. It's an acquired taste.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What about specialized medical care?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Iceland handles most care well. For rare specialties or complex cases, travel to Denmark (Copenhagen) is common and often covered by Icelandic system. Having international insurance that covers Denmark provides additional security. Plan for occasional medical travel if needed.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Ready to Compare Options?</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Get quotes from providers with Nordic coverage for Iceland.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-0">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Insurance requirements, visa regulations, and healthcare access rules change regularly. Always verify current requirements with Icelandic Directorate of Immigration and consult with a licensed insurance professional.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
